&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation&quot;&gt;Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opener:
Start in &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5492&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fire Attunement&#x2F;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5494&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Air Attunement&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5692&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dragon&#x27;s Tooth (ü™Ñüî•2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5736&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Firestorm (Optional)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5492&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fire Attunement (üî•&#x2F;üî•)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then press all of your skills off cooldown. It honestly doesn&#x27;t matter too much which order you push your buttons in, as long as you try your best to hit them off cooldown. I personally press most of my buttons from left to right on the keyboard for this build, as it is easier that way.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do take note that some skills have no cooldown and can be simultaneously cast with other skills. These are:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5678&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fire Shield&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40183&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Primordial Stance&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;alternative-traits-skills&quot;&gt;Alternative traits&#x2F;skills&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5635&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Arcane Echo (in ranged fights (Fire Wall x 2) or when more CC (Gale x 2) is needed)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44926&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Stone Resonance (open world or for survivability)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5536&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Lightning Flash (for kiting&#x2F;ball collection)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;crowd-control&quot;&gt;Crowd Control&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have to prepare your CC skills in advance. Staying in air is a DPS loss. You do play DPS catch-up after doing the necessary CC and resetting your opener which triggers &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2131&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Elements of Rage.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CC Rotation 400-800:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5494&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Air Attunement üå©Ô∏è&#x2F;üî•&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5492&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fire Attunement üî•&#x2F;üå©Ô∏è&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5635&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Arcane Echo (Optional)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5562&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gale (üå©Ô∏è5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5562&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gale (If Echoed)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opener&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use Fire-only skills and utilities while you are attuned to üå©Ô∏è&#x2F;üî• or üî•&#x2F;üå©Ô∏è. Due to the nature of how Weaver works, on certain fights where there is no damage during CC phase, this may result in a DPS increase. However repeatedly doing &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5494&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Air Attunement will result in a DPS loss because of how Inferno works.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;It may not be worthwhile to echo &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5687&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Updraft if you are taking dagger because it does a lot less CC.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;Additional CC can be done, for example attuning to water and bringing arcane wave, but these will result in a massive drop in DPS.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;video&quot;&gt;Video&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
